HEADWORD: Crowkeeper
<hw>Crow"keep`er</hw> <pr>(-k?p`?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person
employed to scare off crows; hence, a scarecrow.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Scaring the ladies like a <qex>crowkeeper</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crown</ent>⟦br⟧
